Of all the rainbows, I love the garden ones the most. They happen right after a heavy downpour. You know the sort, when the sky goes dark and the rain batters the window. Then, suddenly, the sun peeps out.

If I rush to the back door, I can see it. A bright arch of colour stretches right over the neighbour's fence and lands in our green grass. It looks close enough to touch! The red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, and violet shine against the grey clouds. 

The best bit is the wet grass. The raindrops left on the lawn catch the light. They sparkle like tiny diamonds. The air smells fresh and earthy, like soil and summer flowers. 

Sometimes, a double rainbow appears. A fainter arch sits above the bright one. It feels like pure magic. I always run outside to find the end of it, hoping for a pot of gold. I never find the gold, but seeing those beautiful colours over my garden makes me feel very happy indeed. [end of text]


